# AWS S3 Blocking and Access Control

1. Created an S3 bucket:

* sugandha-test-bucket

2. Created a custom bucket access policy:

* TestBucketAccess

3. Attached the bucket access policy to:

* Alpha
* s3-user

4. Verified that:

* Alpha user could access the bucket
* s3-user could access the bucket

5. Tested bucket access using direct S3 bucket URL.

6. Created an explicit deny policy:

* DenyTestBucketAccess

7. Configured blocking for:

* billing-user
* developer-user
* admin-user

8. Attached the explicit deny policy to restricted IAM users.

9. Verified that blocked users received:

* Access Denied
* Insufficient permissions

10. Learned the difference between:

* bucket listing permissions
* bucket object access permissions

11. Learned AWS IAM concepts:

* Allow Policy
* Explicit Deny Policy
* Deny overrides Allow
* Least Privilege Access

12. Used the direct S3 bucket URL for permission testing:
    https://us-east-1.console.aws.amazon.com/s3/buckets/sugandha-test-bucket
